President Donald Trump recently announced a $16 billion aid package for American farmers aimed at softening the financial blow created by the ongoing trade war with China. “Our farmers will be greatly helped,” Trump said during a press event in the Roosevelt Room at the White House. “The 16 billion [dollar] funds will help keep our cherished farms thriving.” It would be recalled that talks between the two countries ended without a deal as Trump imposed another round of tariffs on $200 billion of Chinese goods. Both Trump and President Xi Jinping of China have signaled that they are prepared for a long fight, if necessary. Watch Trump below on his twitter handle addressing American farmers on Wednesday and giving the hope of a bright future: 